text: The lipspot moray eel (Gymnothorax chilospilus), also known as the textile moray, white-lipped moray or white-lipped reef eel,Common names for Gymnothorax chilospilus at www.fishbase.org. is a moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.Gymnothorax chilospilus at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Pieter Bleeker in 1864. It is named for a distinct white spot on the lower lip near the corner of the mouth. ==References== ==External links== * Fishes of Australia : Gymnothorax chilospilus lipspot moray Category:Marine fish of Northern Australia lipspot moray
